## ITERATION 40 BODY

title: "039 — Extract Vehicle Marker Component + Introduce Radar Marker Structure"
description: "Isolate vehicle marker markup and styles into a dedicated component so marker UI can be refined rapidly without affecting the rest of the dashboard."

:::GOALS

Move all vehicle marker rendering concerns into a single dedicated component.

This component must fully own:

- marker markup
- marker sizing
- halo/ring structure
- heading indicator
- glyph rendering
- selected state styling
- status state styling

The rest of the app should treat the vehicle marker as a black box.

Introduce a single unified marker design based on a radar marker pattern that separates:

- identity
- heading
- operational ring

This creates a stable foundation for continued marker experimentation without touching map, routes, overlays, or panel layout.

:::END

:::TASKS

Create or refactor a dedicated `VehicleMarker` component so all marker UI is encapsulated there.

Move marker-specific structure and styling out of generic map or overlay code and into this component.

Ensure the map layer only passes vehicle data and selection state into `VehicleMarker`.

The component must support these responsibilities internally:

- render the center identity glyph
- render a heading indicator
- render status-driven ring styling
- render selected state treatment
- render degraded / critical / offline visual states

Replace the current cramped marker treatment with a unified radar marker structure.

Implement the radar marker structure explicitly as follows:

1. Outer operational ring
- Increase overall marker circumference substantially relative to the current implementation.
- The ring should read as a large surrounding operational ring, not a thin decorative outline.
- Preserve status coloring behavior for normal, degraded, critical, and offline.

2. Center identity marker
- Keep the central glyph as the fastest-readable element.
- The glyph remains centered and visually dominant over heading decoration.
- Preserve readability against satellite terrain.

3. Heading wedge
- Move heading expression out of the cramped center treatment.
- Render a clear directional wedge associated with the marker.
- The wedge must rotate with vehicle heading.
- The wedge should read immediately as direction, without competing with the center glyph.

Style all marker-related elements inside the dedicated component stylesheet or marker-specific style block.

Keep one consistent marker treatment for all vehicles.

Do not render multiple heading variants in the live UI.

Do not modify route rendering, alert overlay, camera overlay, fleet cards, or panel layout as part of this iteration.

:::END

:::ACCEPTANCE

- Vehicle marker UI is isolated to its own dedicated component.
- Marker markup and styles can be changed without touching the rest of the app.
- The marker uses a radar marker structure with:
  - large outer ring
  - central identity glyph
  - clear heading wedge
- Heading is more readable than before.
- The center glyph remains the quickest element to recognize.
- All vehicles use the same marker treatment.

:::END